entries.s_20: It's done, if that's what you mean.
entries.s_22: That's exactly what it means. Very good. My business associates thank you for keeping their trade safe. Here is your payment.
entries.s_28: I'd love to do nothing more than chat, but I'm busy.
entries.s_29: Ah. You look like the kind of person that can help me.
entries.s_30: Sgt. Snopel sent me to you.
entries.s_31: Take care of that base. I won't pay you until the job is done. You should have all the information that you need in your journal.
entries.s_32: Of course he did. I have a job for you. Won't be too easy, but shouldn't kill ya either. A bunch of sand pirates are interfering with my business partners.
entries.s_34: Any transport that gets within a thousand meters of their base tends to have some unfortunate accidents...at the end of blaster bolts.
entries.s_35: So what am I to do?
entries.s_36: Simple. You go to their base, kill their leader, and make sure that no one will be able to use the base again.
entries.s_9: Good work. You are a credit to your Senior Officers.
